The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 4: The dispute in the Ranbaxy promoter family took an ugly turn today with one section approaching the police against the other, alleging ?illegal construction? at the family house in the city. Ranbaxy CEO Malvinder Singh claimed a complaint has been filed alleging goons sent by his uncle Analjit Singh had threatened his mother Nimmi Singh, who tried to prevent them from an illegal construction at the family house at 15 Aurangzeb Road. The house is a disputed property. The complaint was filed by Nimmi Singh. Analjit Singh could not be contacted as he is out of the country.

 Mumbai, July 4: Indoco Remedies has acquired a 100 per cent stake in La Nova Chem (India) Pvt Ltd. Following the acquisition, La Nova Chem has become a subsidiary of Indoco Remedies, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Mumbai, July 4: Procter and Gamble India Holdings has recently acquired a 41.02 per cent stake in Gillette India, representing 1.33 crore shares of the company.

 New Delhi, July 4: Vedanta Resources has invited preliminary bids to set up a 2,400-mwe nuclear power plant in India, although the government is yet to decide on allowing private companies in the sector.




